Description:
Sherpa 6 is looking for various levels of Software Engineers to join our team in beautiful Littleton, Colorado. If you are looking for career development and growth opportunities, both technically and professionally, all while supporting our nation's heroes then there is no better spot for you. Our company is growing rapidly and we are looking for highly motivated and talented engineers to fill key roles.
As a Service Disabled Veteran Owned Small Business, we know what it means to serve. We have made it our mission to be the leaders in solutions that protect and give our Warfighters the edge they need when put into harm’s way. We provide solutions, where solutions don’t exist. Are you a passionate professional, ready to create solutions for our Warfighters? Join our team today!
www.sherpa6.com

Primary Responsibilities:
As the successful Software Engineer for Sherpa 6 you'll have the opportunity to work hands-on with our amazing engineering team, execute forward thinking skills and develop software for a variety of platforms. The Software Engineer must be at ease working in an Agile environment with little supervision, and act as a subject matter expert for software development and engineering. This will include:
Coding and testing software based upon software specifications and designs;
Analyzing and studying complex system requirements;
Designing software tools and subsystems to support software reuse and domain software development;
Using sound software engineering principles to ensure that developed code is modifiable, efficient, reliable, understandable, and fault tolerant;
Providing software process management and control throughout the coding portion of the software development process.

